The learner passes the essential phases of starting a business: assessing their entrepreneurial qualities, devising a business idea and developing it according to the business process.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course enables the learner to participate in the business process for making calculated decisions about planning their further career (e.g. working as an entrepreneur or entrepreneurial employee). The learner can develop creative thinking, learn the principles of entrepreneurial behaviour and obtain knowledge about identifying business opportunities as well as about developing, evaluating, and implementing business ideas in different business environments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) analyses themselves and their role in a team and business processes; 2) applyes the methods for devising, developing and evaluating business ideas; 3) analyses business processes and the business environment as well as their impact on a planned enterprise; 4) presents their ideas reasonably and convincingly, including their planned business model; 5) plans development and marketing activities.
